                <h1>The Delicious Evolution of Tamales: A Historical Journey</h1>
                <p>Tamales have a rich history that dates back to ancient Mesoamerican cultures, such as the Aztecs and Mayans, who used masa (corn dough) to wrap various fillings. Originally portable and durable, they played a key role in rituals and everyday meals. Today, tamales are enjoyed worldwide, with diverse regional variations, especially in Latin America.</p>
